</div>
			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Scopophobia</h1>
									<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
									<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"><span class="mw-redirectedfrom">  (Redirected from <a href="/w/index.php?title=Ophthalmophobia&amp;redirect=no" title="Ophthalmophobia">Ophthalmophobia</a>)</span></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><p><b>Scopophobia</b>, <b>scoptophobia</b>, or <b>ophthalmophobia</b> is an <a href="/wiki/Anxiety_disorder" title="Anxiety disorder">anxiety disorder</a> characterized by a <a href="/wiki/Morbid_fear" title="Morbid fear" class="mw-redirect">morbid fear</a> of being seen or <a href="/wiki/Staring" title="Staring">stared</a> at by others.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> Scopophobia can also be associated with a pathological fear of drawing attention to oneself.<sup id="cite_ref-Duffey_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Duffey-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>The term <i>scopophobia</i> comes from the <a href="/wiki/Ancient_Greek" title="Ancient Greek">Greek</a> σκοπέω <i>skopeō</i>, "look to, examine",<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup> and φόβος <i>phobos</i>, "fear".<sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4"><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup> <i>Ophthalmophobia</i> comes from the Greek ὀφθαλμός <i>ophthalmos</i>, "eye".<sup id="cite_ref-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-5"><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p></p>
<div id="toc" class="toc">
<div id="toctitle">
